It looks good to me by reading the code.

But I'm wondering how can we test/verify reliably the partial write situations?
Can it be made as unit-test or some kind of stress test?

what is a partial write situation?  When there are multiple socket reads for a single http request?  If so, this test already tests that.  http2 requests are read/written in chunks, so there's no such thing as a request that takes a single write.

In addition, the patchset prior to this has lots of tests for partial writes of varying sizes.  PTAL
Thanks for clarification
